{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Be merciful to me, God, for man wants to swallow me up. All day long, he attacks and oppresses me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My enemies want to swallow me up all day long, for they are many who fight proudly against me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "When I am afraid, I will put my trust in you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "In God, I praise his word. In God, I put my trust. I will not be afraid. What can flesh do to me?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "All day long they twist my words. All their thoughts are against me for evil."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They conspire and lurk, watching my steps."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They are eager to take my life."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Shall they escape by iniquity? In anger cast down the peoples, God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You count my wanderings. You put my tears into your container."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Aren’t they in your book?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Then my enemies shall turn back in the day that I call. I know this: that God is for me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "In God, I will praise his word. In Yahweh, I will praise his word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have put my trust in God. I will not be afraid."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "What can man do to me?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your vows are on me, God. I will give thank offerings to you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For you have delivered my soul from death, and prevented my feet from falling,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "that I may walk before God in the light of the living."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}